Catriona Laing, British High Commissioner to Nigeria has reacted to Dr. Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala’s emergence as the Director-General of the WTO. DAILY POST had reported that Dr Okonjo-Iweala scaled through screening processes to emerge the WTO Director-General and is to commence her tenure on the 1st of March 2021. WTO confirmed her appointment at a special meeting of the General Council, following a selection process that included eight candidates from around the world. In a congratulatory message on her Twitter account, the British High Commissioner, Laing said she was delighted to hear the good news. “So delighted to hear this now confirmed. @NOIweala is the best possible leader for @wto at the most challenging of times. “It feels so good to have a Nigerian woman in this top job. Congratulations,” she wrote.